CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1967, pg. 1A, reads: "To the Point - A delegation of McKees Rocks protestors of the cut-off of the anti-poverty war's community action programs carried this mock coffin lacking 'insides' at Monday's Gateway Center demonstration. They  wanted to throw it into the river off the end of the 'Bridge To Nowhere' but police made them be content with throwing it in at The Point.  It did not sink of sail away but stuck to the Point. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men from McKees Rocks carrying mock casket with signs reading "For Immediate Action Keep Your Local Community Program Alive" and "Dollars Fight Poverty not Promises,"  for protest against cutbacks of poverty program, the Point, Downtown
